This paper examines the support for various HTTP methods on the web, which is a topic related to web development and web services. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.WEB. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing a large collection of URIs, which could fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS) or information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the security implications of HTTP methods, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) or cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions the implementation of HTTP methods, which could fall under the category of programming languages (cs.PL).
